title: Cannabinoid
summary: Cannabinoids (/kəˈnæbənɔɪdzˌ ˈkænəbənɔɪdz/) are compounds found in cannabis.[1][2] The most notable cannabinoid is the phytocannabinoid tetrahydrocannabinol (THC) (Delta9-THC or Delta8-THC), the primary psychoactive compound in cannabis.[3][4] Cannabidiol (CBD) is another major constituent of the plant.[5] At least 113 distinct cannabinoids have been isolated from cannabis.[6]
